      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat.",
    "Add the curry paste and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the bell peppers and cook until they start to soften, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the coconut milk, lime juice, fish sauce, and palm sugar, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 10 minutes, or until the peppers are tender.",
    "Deglaze the pan with a little water if the curry starts to stick.",
    "Season the curry with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve hot over rice or noodles."
  ],
